      "comment_id" : 119094805,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "One reason to keep the constructor <code>public</code> besides backwards compatibility is that it&#39;s slightly faster to create an <code>Integer</code> object without checking the cache, if you know it&#39;s probably not going to be in the cache. At some point the cost of doing a cache check for every value outweighs the extra cost of garbage-collecting the few extra objects that would have been in the cache."
